  "body": "See [Jveux’s React version](http://jsfiddle.net/vjeux/KbWJ2/9) of [Infinity](http://airbnb.github.io/infinity/demo-on.html). I know that it’s not an updated version of React, but I get the same result with 0.11.2\n\nIt works seamlessly until you let go of the trackpad/magic mouse (you know, when momentum scrolling kicks in). The scrolling suddenly stops when re-rendering.\n\nHere’s a reduced test-case of my own experiment where I get the same result: http://f.cl.ly/items/0I3l3V0634253F2n2t0x/react-infinity.html\n\nIf you’d only change the color of the visible items vs. the non-visible ones, it wouldn’t lag at all. I’m a little bit lost as to why it stops… been struggling for a few days trying different ways to implement Infinity with React.\n\nKnown issue? (if issue there is)\nAny hints/workarounds?\n",
